# =============================================================================
# AUTH SERVER .ENV
# =============================================================================
# NOTE: This file is for reference only. The auth server uses the root .env
# file at the monorepo root level (../../.env)
# =============================================================================
#
# For actual configuration, edit: ../../.env (root .env file)
#
# Required variables for auth server:
# - POSTGRES_DB
# - POSTGRES_USER
# - POSTGRES_PASSWORD
# - BETTER_AUTH_SECRET
# - FRONTEND_URL
#
# Optional variables:
# - PATIENT_FRONTEND_URL (for additional CORS)
# - SMTP_HOST, SMTP_PORT, SMTP_USER, SMTP_PASS, SMTP_FROM (for email verification)
# - HASURA_ACTION_SECRET (shared secret for validating Hasura action requests)
#
# NOT NEEDED (unused by auth server):
# - DATABASE_URL (auth server constructs connection string from POSTGRES_* vars)
# - HASURA_DATABASE_URL (not used)
# - AUTH_SERVER_URL (not used)
# - API_URL (not used)
# - HASURA_GRAPHQL_ADMIN_SECRET (action handlers query PostgreSQL directly)
#
# See root .env.example for detailed configuration options.
# =============================================================================
